## Appendix B: Proof of the Crossover Point

**Theorem B.1 (Crossover Point).** For the Pegasus graph (D-Wave Advantage), the crossover point $N_c$ satisfies $N_c \le 12$.

*Proof.* For $K_N$, the minimal minor embedding requires approximately $N$ qubits per logical variable, giving $\text{qubits} \approx N^2$. For the P-Model, $\text{qubits} \approx 3N$. Solving $3N < N^2$ gives $N > 3$. However, the constant factors matter. For $N=12$, $K_{12}$ embedding requires $\approx 144$ qubits, while P-Model requires $\approx 36$ qubits. For $N=8$, the difference is $64$ vs $24$ qubits. Thus the crossover occurs well before $N=8$. ∎

